==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scholion
<hw>Scho"li*on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<def>A scholium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A judgment which follows immediately from another is sometimes
called a corollary, or consectary . . . One which illustrates the
science where it appears, but is not an integral part of it, is a
<qex>scholion</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Abp. Thomson (Laws of
Thought).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scholium</ent>⟦br⟧
